LudoTrace is a session black box for Fallout 4. Every time you save, it writes an impartial record of your session to a plain JSONL file — kills, quests, locations, inventory, combat events, SPECIAL changes. No opinions, no overlays, no ESP. Just the data.

What you do with it is up to you. Paste it into an AI for coaching, comedy reacts, or a stat breakdown. Feed it into your own tools. Read it yourself. An example AI prompt is included.

No ESP, no MCM, no holotape.

[size=5][b]What it logs[/b][/size]

Every session captures:

[list]
[*]Character snapshot at start and end — level, SPECIAL, bobbleheads collected, ammo counts, aid inventory[/*]
[*]Locations visited (deduped — each location logged once per session)[/*]
[*]Kills — target name, killer (you or a companion), in-game time[/*]
[*]Legendary enemy kills and loot examinations[/*]
[*]Quest stage changes and completions[/*]
[*]Bobblehead proximity alerts — notified when you enter a bobblehead location[/*]
[*]SPECIAL changes (bobblehead pickups, disease effects)[/*]
[*]Aid item and chem usage[/*]
[*]Misc stats — caps found, creatures killed, items scrapped, chests looted, and more[/*]
[*]Combat state changes for you and companions[/*]
[*]Limb cripple and heal events[/*]
[/list]

The log is plain JSONL (one JSON object per line) written to:

[code]Fallout 4\lt_fo4_events.jsonl[/code]
example:

[code]{"type":"session_start","date":"2288-02-28","game_time":"07:50","level":40,"name":"Rhea","special":{"S":11,"P":7,"E":4,"C":7,"I":8,"A":6,"L":7},"bobbleheads":["Charisma","Intelligence","Strength"],"ammo":[{"name":"Mini Nuke","form_id":"0x000E6B2E","count":14},{"name":"Plasma Cartridge","form_id":"0x0001DBB7","count":912}],"aid":[{"name":"Stimpak","form_id":"0x00023736","count":252},{"name":"Jet","form_id":"0x000366C5","count":3}]}
{"type":"location","name":"Vault 88","game_time":"18:17"}
{"type":"kill","target":"Mole Rat Brood Mother","killer":"Rhea","game_time":"18:40"}
{"type":"near_collectible","category":"bobblehead","name":"Endurance","location":"Poseidon Energy Turbine 18-F","game_time":"18:55"}
{"type":"av_change","av":"Perception","from":7,"to":1,"time":"19:04"}
{"type":"level","to":41,"perks":[{"name":"Rifleman","rank":3},{"name":"Sneak","rank":2}],"time":"19:30"}
{"type":"quest_stage","quest":"Explore Vault 88","stage":150,"time":"20:14"}
{"type":"kill","target":"Legendary Alpha Deathclaw","killer":"Rhea","game_time":"22:38"}
{"type":"stat","stat":"Stimpaks Taken","value":187,"time":"22:38"}
{"type":"used","category":"chem","item":"Jet","game_time":"01:52"}
{"type":"kill","target":"Mirelurk Queen","killer":"Rhea","game_time":"00:57"}
{"type":"session_end","date":"2288-02-28","game_time":"03:40","level":41,"name":"Rhea","special":{"S":11,"P":7,"E":4,"C":7,"I":8,"A":6,"L":7},"bobbleheads":["Charisma","Intelligence","Strength"],"ammo":[{"name":"Mini Nuke","form_id":"0x000E6B2E","count":14},{"name":"Plasma Cartridge","form_id":"0x0001DBB7","count":912}],"aid":[{"name":"Stimpak","form_id":"0x00023736","count":250},{"name":"Jet","form_id":"0x000366C5","count":3}]}[/code]

You can read it, parse it, or feed it into any tool you like. The Claude.ai coaching workflow is built in, but the log is yours.

[size=5][b]The coaching workflow[/b][/size]

[b]1. Play.[/b] Load any save — the mod registers automatically on load and starts recording. Save when you're done.

[b]2. Open Claude.ai.[/b] Start a new chat at claude.ai (free account).

[b]3. Paste the prompt + your log.[/b] A coaching prompt is included as [font=Courier New]coaching_prompt.md[/font] in the zip. Paste it, then paste the contents of [font=Courier New]lt_fo4_events.jsonl[/font] below it.

[b]4. Get coaching.[/b] Claude reads your session and gives you specific, actionable feedback based on what actually happened — not generic tips.

[size=5][b]Example output when piped through Claude[/b][/size]

[i](From a real session — level 40 character in Vault 88)[/i]

[quote]You have 14 Mini Nukes and fought a Legendary Alpha Deathclaw for 37 in-game minutes without using one. A Fat Man shot would have ended that fight in seconds.

Your Perception was knocked to 1 three times during the Vault 88 mole rat fights — that's the DLC disease stacking, not limb damage. Visit a doctor before your next session or your VATS accuracy is gutted.

912 Plasma Cartridges, zero used this session. With INT 8 you almost certainly have Science! ranks. A plasma weapon shreds the armored targets you're struggling with.[/quote]

The coaching references your actual inventory, your actual kills, your actual quests — not a generic build guide.

[size=5][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://f4se.silverlock.org/]F4SE[/url][/*]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fallout4/mods/104159]Hydra[/url][/*]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fallout4/mods/47327]Address Library for F4SE Plugins[/url][/*]
[/list]

[size=5][b]Install[/b][/size]

Drop the contents of the zip into your Fallout 4 [font=Courier New]Data\[/font] folder, or install via Vortex or Mod Organizer 2.

